-- BG Group up on talk of Exxon Mobil interest: traders
-- 
-- Thu Sep 4, 2008 6:03am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/04/us-bg-shares-idUSL413111620080904

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - Shares in BG Group ( BG.L ) rose as much as 5.1 percent on Thursday as traders cited market talk of bid interest from Exxon Mobil ( XOM.N ). 

 BG declined to comment. "Heard that Exxon were sniffing," one trader said. More than 6.5 million BG shares changed hands by 4:56 a.m. EDT, compared with a full-day average of 11.2 million shares in the past 30 days. BG was up 3.9 percent, while the FTSE 100  .FTSE  was up 0.2 percent. (Additional reporting by Dan Lalor) (Reporting by  Dominic Lau , Atul Prakash and Michael Taylor)